****My findings****
This is actually a task management system, it Create tasks, View/list tasks, Update tasks (status, priority, due date, tags), Delete tasks, Filter tasks (by status, priority, overdue), View statistics about tasks
Persist tasks to a file (tasks.json). cli.py, reads command-line input (like create, list, delete), Converts input into arguments, Calls functions in TaskManager, Prints results. models.py is the data model layer or structure, its is more like a blueprint. app.py is the logic or control layer. storage is basically for saing everything or persisting everything.

